headline: France is still trading uranium with Russia, nearly four years after Ukraine invasion

headline: Half of new immigrants in France are students or refugees
description: Legal immigration flows continue to rise, while economic immigration is declining and regularizations are falling, according to Interior Ministry figures published on Tuesday.

headline: Work-related cancers remain a blind spot in France's public health system
description: A study conducted by doctors and occupational sociologists at the Avignon Hospital Center on over 500 lymphoma patients found there was a 'massive underestimation' of work-related cancers in France.

headline: Richard Ford: 'I tell my European friends how it feels not to understand my country'
description: The novelist expresses concern, in an op-ed for Le Monde, about the direction his country has taken under President Donald Trump. He laments that Americans do not appear to pay attention to the erosion of their constitutional rights, nor do they grasp how difficult it will be to turn back.
